\subsection{Pairwise basic-open intersection helpers (iter-056)}

Iter-056 (this iteration) appends two thin foundational helpers about pairwise intersections of basic-open cover members. The Čech complex on a basic-open cover $\mathcal{U} = \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s$ at degree 1 indexes pairs $(i, j) \in s \times s$ and assigns the sheaf $F$ evaluated at the pairwise intersection $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,i \sqcap \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,j$. By Mathlib's $\mathtt{Scheme.basicOpen\_mul}$ ($X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,(f \cdot g) = X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f \sqcap X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,g$), this intersection identifies with the basic open of the product $i.1 \cdot j.1 \in \Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$. Iter-056 packages this identification + the affine-membership transport into named project-local theorems so the iter-057+ Čech-evaluation argument can apply them directly via $\mathtt{simp}$ / $\mathtt{rw}$.

The strategic value: factors out the binary-intersection identification from iter-057+ Koszul acyclicity. The full $n$-ary generalisation to $\mathtt{Fin}\,(n+1)$ indexing (or $\mathtt{Finset.prod}$) is deferred to iter-057+ when the Čech-evaluation argument structure clarifies the natural shape (the $n$-ary form has a non-trivial empty-product edge case $\mathtt{basicOpen}\,1 = U \neq \top$ that complicates the $\mathtt{Finset}$ version).

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Pairwise basic-open intersection equals basic open of product, iter-056]
  \label{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_inter_eq_basicOpen_mul}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.basicOpenCover_inter_eq_basicOpen_mul}
  \uses{def:Scheme_basicOpenCover}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathtt{of}\,k))$, $U$ an open of $C.\mathtt{left}$, $s \subseteq \Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$, and $i, j : s$. Then
  \[
    \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,i \sqcap \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,j \,=\, C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,(i.1 \cdot j.1).
  \]
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}\leanok
  Direct application of Mathlib's $\mathtt{Scheme.basicOpen\_mul}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/Scheme.lean}), which states $X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,(f \cdot g) = X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f \sqcap X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,g$. After unfolding $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}$ (which expands to $\mathtt{fun}\,f \mapsto C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,(f : \Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U))$), the LHS becomes $C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,i.1 \sqcap C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,j.1$. The forward direction of Mathlib's lemma rewrites this to $C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,(i.1 \cdot j.1)$; we want the reverse equality, hence the $\mathtt{.symm}$ in the body. Body: $\mathtt{by}\,\mathtt{unfold}\,\mathtt{basicOpenCover};\,\mathtt{exact}\,(\mathtt{Scheme.basicOpen\_mul}\,C.\mathtt{left}\,\_\,\_).\mathtt{symm}$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-056 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms $[\propext, \Classical.\mathtt{choice}, \Quot.\mathtt{sound}]$.
\end{proof}

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Pairwise basic-open intersection on affine is itself affine, iter-056]
  \label{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_inter_isAffineOpen}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.basicOpenCover_inter_isAffineOpen}
  \uses{def:Scheme_basicOpenCover, thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_inter_eq_basicOpen_mul}
  Under $(h_U : \IsAffineOpen\,U)$, $(s : \Set\,\Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U))$, and $i, j : s$, $\IsAffineOpen\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,i \sqcap \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,j)$.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}\leanok
  Combines Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_inter_eq_basicOpen_mul} (rewriting the intersection as a single basic open of $i.1 \cdot j.1$) with Mathlib's $\mathtt{IsAffineOpen.basicOpen}$ (which states for $h_U : \IsAffineOpen\,U$ and $f : \Gamma(X, U)$, $\IsAffineOpen\,(X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f)$). Body: $\mathtt{by}\,\mathtt{unfold}\,\mathtt{basicOpenCover};\,\mathtt{rw}\,[\leftarrow\mathtt{Scheme.basicOpen\_mul}];\,\mathtt{exact}\,h_U.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,\_$. The $\mathtt{rw}\,[\leftarrow\mathtt{Scheme.basicOpen\_mul}]$ step is load-bearing — without it, the intersection shape from $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,i \sqcap \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,j$ doesn't directly land on the single-basic-open form needed by $\mathtt{IsAffineOpen.basicOpen}$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-056 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

Generalises iter-054's $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_isAffineOpen}$ (single-index affine membership) to pairwise intersections. Used by iter-057+ Čech evaluation: each finite intersection of basic opens is itself affine, which is the inductive step for the Koszul alternating-sum argument (Stacks 03F7 / Hartshorne III.4.5 / Eisenbud Commutative Algebra §17 Koszul resolution).

